The National Coronavirus Command Council will brief the media on Monday following President Cyril Ramaphosa’s address to the nation on Sunday, on the government's further plans to combat the spread of COVID-19. PRETORIA - The National Coronavirus Command Council will brief the country on Monday following President Cyril Ramaphosa’s address to the nation on Sunday on government's further plans to combat the spread of COVID-19. COVID-19: SA to remain on level 3 lockdown The Amended Regulations will be explained by CoGTA Minister Dr Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma, Minister of Trade, Industry & Competition Ebrahim Patel and the Minister of Justice and Correctional Services Ronald Lamola. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 